VIConclusion
Based on realistic scenarios for commercial AI data centres and HPC centres, and a linear analytical model that takes into account key server and data centre parameters, we have simulated the reduction in emissions achievable through for geographic load shifting. We conclude that the reductions in emissions from geographic load shifting are small (typically less than five percent) for realistic scenarios for both commercial data centres and HPC centres. Much larger reductions in emissions are needed to counter the current growth in global data centre capacity.